- cs.SI (Social and Information Networks) is the most likely category as the paper deals with large graphs and their structure, which is a common topic in social and information networks research.
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is also likely as the paper presents a novel way to summarize the structure of large graphs, which involves clustering and density estimation, both of which are common topics in data structures and algorithms research.
- cs.LG (Machine Learning) is another likely category as the paper uses unsupervised learning techniques to extract patterns from large graphs and also uses the method as a preparation step for supervised learning.
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper presents a novel method for analyzing large graphs, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence research.
- cs.IT (Information Theory) is also a possible category as the paper uses a model selection technique with data-dependent prior and obtains an exact evaluation criterion for the posterior probability of edge density estimation models, which are common topics in information theory research.
